; The web app pins react@19, but react-leaflet@4 and react-responsive-modal
; peer-require react@^18. pnpm tolerates this (warning only) and the app builds
; and runs fine; npm, however, hard-fails with ERESOLVE. The GitHub Pages build
; workflows (.github/workflows/*.yml) run `npm i`, so without this they break.
; legacy-peer-deps makes npm resolve like pnpm does. (pnpm ignores this key.)
;
; Proper long-term fix: upgrade react-leaflet to v5 (native react-19 support) or
; migrate the CI workflows to pnpm.
legacy-peer-deps=true
